+ Using the axiom for building sets pairwise, prove that the following sets are distinct: $\phi, \{\phi\}, \{\{\phi\}\}, \{\phi, \{\phi\}\}$.

Hypothesis:

$$
  \begin{align}
    \forall x, x \in \{a\} & \leftrightarrow & x = a \tag{1build} \\
    \forall x, x \in \{a, b\} & \leftrightarrow & (x = a) \vee (x = b) \tag{2build}
  \end{align}
$$

Proof:

By the above properties of equality being transitive, to show that a certain collection of sets are distinct, it is sufficient to show pairwise inequality upto transitivity.

$$
  \begin{align*}
    \phi \in \{\phi\} & \rightarrow \phi \neq \{\phi\} & \textrm{by (1build)} \\
    \{\phi\} \in \{\{\phi\}\} & \rightarrow \{\phi\} \neq \{\{\phi\}\} & \textrm{by (1build)} \\
    \phi \in \{\phi, \{\phi\}\} \wedge \{\phi\} \in \{\phi, \{\phi\}\} & \rightarrow \textrm{no two are equal} & \textrm{by (2build)}
  \end{align*}
$$

