+ Show that, for any three sets $A, B, C$, $A \subseteq B \wedge B \subseteq A \rightarrow A = B$, and $A \subsetneq B \subsetneq C \rightarrow A \subsetneq C$.

Hypothesis:

$$
  \begin{align}
    A \in C \wedge A = B & \rightarrow B \in C \tag{subst} \\
    A = B & \leftrightarrow \forall x, x \in A \leftrightarrow x \in B \tag{eq} \\
    A \subseteq B & \leftrightarrow \forall x, x \in A \rightarrow x \in B \tag{subset-eq} \\
    A \subsetneq B & \leftrightarrow A \subseteq B \wedge A \neq B \tag{subset-neq}
  \end{align}
$$

Proof:

$$
  \begin{matrix}
    A \subseteq B \wedge B \subseteq A & \rightarrow & \forall x, x \in A \leftrightarrow x \in B & \textrm{by (subset-eq) and intuition} \\
    & \leftrightarrow & A = B & \textrm{by (eq)} \\
    A \subsetneq B \wedge B \subsetneq C & \rightarrow     & A \subseteq B \wedge B \subseteq C & \\
                                         &                 & \wedge & \\
                                         &                 & A \neq B \wedge B \neq C & \textrm{by (subset-neq)} \\
                                         & \rightarrow     & A \subseteq B \wedge A \subseteq C & \\
                                         &                 & \wedge & \\
                                         &                 & A \neq C & \textrm{by (subst)} \\
                                         & \rightarrow     & \forall x, x \in A \rightarrow x \in B & \textrm{by (subset-eq)} \\
                                         &                 & \wedge & \\
                                         &                 & \forall x, x \in B \rightarrow x \in C & \textrm{by (subset-eq)} \\
                                         & \rightarrow     & \forall x, x \in A \rightarrow x \in C & \textrm{by intuition} \\
                                         &                 & \wedge & \\
                                         &                 & A \neq C & \\
                                         & \leftrightarrow & A \subsetneq C & \textrm{by (subset-neq)}
  \end{matrix}
$$

